# Check API Documentation First

When working with **any external API** (especially GoHighLevel / GHL), always:

1. **Look up the official docs** before writing integration code or fixing API errors
2. **Use exact parameter names** from the docs (e.g., GHL uses `date` + `endDate`, not `startDate`)
3. **Verify request format** (GET query params vs POST body, snake_case vs camelCase)

## GHL Opportunities Search

- Endpoint: `GET /opportunities/search`
- Docs: https://marketplace.gohighlevel.com/docs/ghl/opportunities/search-opportunity
- Date params: `date` (start) and `endDate` (end)

## General Rule

Don't guess or assume API parameters. Fetch the documentation and match the spec exactly.
